<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Scaling Strategies - Node.js Interview Playground</title>
    <%- include('../partials/styles') %>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <%- include('../partials/header') %>
        <%- include('../partials/nav') %>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Scaling Strategies</h2>
            <p>Understanding horizontal vs vertical scaling and when to use each approach.</p>
            
            <h3>Vertical Scaling (Scale Up)</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>// Add more resources to existing server
- Increase CPU cores
- Increase RAM
- Increase storage
- Upgrade hardware</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Pros:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Simpler architecture</li>
                    <li>No code changes needed</li>
                    <li>Better for single-threaded bottlenecks</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Cons:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Limited by hardware maximums</li>
                    <li>Single point of failure</li>
                    <li>More expensive at scale</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h3>Horizontal Scaling (Scale Out)</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>// Add more servers
- Multiple instances
- Load balancer
- Stateless application
- Shared state (Redis, DB)</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Pros:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Unlimited scaling potential</li>
                    <li>Better fault tolerance</li>
                    <li>Cost-effective with commodity hardware</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Cons:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>More complex architecture</li>
                    <li>Requires stateless design</li>
                    <li>Need load balancing</li>
                    <li>Shared state management</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <h3>When to Use Each</h3>
            <div class="topic-grid">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <h3>Vertical Scaling</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Small to medium applications</li>
                        <li>CPU-intensive tasks</li>
                        <li>Single-threaded bottlenecks</li>
                        <li>Simpler deployment</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <h3>Horizontal Scaling</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>High traffic applications</li>
                        <li>Need high availability</li>
                        <li>Stateless applications</li>
                        <li>Cloud-native architecture</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
